t: "They¬†ask you ňĻO Prophetňļ about fighting in the sacred months.¬†Say, ‚ÄúFighting during these months is a great sin. But hindering ňĻothersňļ from the Path of God, rejecting Him, and expelling the worshippers from the Sacred Mosque is ňĻaňļ greater ňĻsinňļ in the sight of God. For persecution¬†is far worse than killing. And they will not stop fighting you until they turn you away from your faith‚ÄĒif they can. And whoever among you renounces their own faith and dies a disbeliever, their deeds will become void in this life and in the Hereafter. It is they who will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever.‚ÄĚ"